-- PRESS DIGEST - Bulgaria - Oct 30
-- 
-- Thu Oct 30, 2014 04:14AM EDT
-- None



SOFIA, Oct 29 (Reuters) - These are some of the main stories in Bulgarian newspapers on Thursday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

-- European People's Party Group chairman Joseph Daul called on Bulgarian political parties to form a center-right government (Trud, Standart, Sega, Presa, Monitor, Capital daily, Duma, 24 Chasa). -- Bulgarian President Rosen Plevneliev will hold meetings with all parties in parliament but this time he will receive them in reverse order starting from the smallest one. Plevneliev expects the new government to be formed before Nov. 10 (Trud, Standart, Presa, Monitor, Capital daily, 24 Chasa). -- French oil major Total's <TOTF.PA> will start hydrocarbon drilling at the Bulgarian Black Sea block Khan Asparuh in the second half of 2015, Exploration Manager at Total E&P Bulgaria Paul Sexton said (Standart, Monitor). PRESA - The share of grey economy in Bulgaria's GDP has dropped from 42.2 percent in 2010 to 32.3 percent in 2014, the Bulgarian Industrial Capital Association's survey showed.